channel.title: Rune-Zero | Need website developers
channel.description:
[center][IMG]http://i40.tinypic.com/2dtb38w.png[/img][/center] [center][b]Base:[/b] [i]Project Insanity[/i] (The original release)[/center] ______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
[center][b]Introduction[/b]:[/center] [i]Hello Moparscape, and welcome to the rune-zero development thread. I would like to start off by saying I know that PI is filled with glitches/bugs but I know with a little time and patience, I can develop something great. My main goal is to make this a player friendly server. It will be eco-based, and every rare will be hard to obtain. In the future, I may make a world 2 for pking, not real sure yet.[/i]
[center][b]Information[/b]:[/center] [i]I plan on rewriting all the skills to my liking. After I finish the skills, I plan on making a couple of custom quests/minigames. I will make daily updates on this thread, however, during the weekdays I have school so I won't be able to updates the thread until I get home.
[b]Note:[/b] I might host this when I finish, or I might just release it. When I get closer to finishing this project, I will add a poll above so you guys can vote.[/i] ______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
[b]KEY:[/b] Green =[b] Complete[/b] Orange =[b] Started[/b] Red = [b]Not started[/b]
[b]Bugs:[/b] All known bugs fixed
[b]Skills:[/b] [i]I haven't began working on the skills yet. Combat is the first thing I am going to work on, after I get combat where I want it, I will begin working on the rest of the skills.[/i]
[b]Media:[/b] [IMG]http://i41.tinypic.com/1zguvko.png[/img]
[b]Positions:[/b] Server developer - 2/2 Client developer - 1/1 Website developer - 2/2
[center][b]Application layout:[/b][/center] [center][code]Name: Age: MSN: What do you want to be: Experience: Proof:[/code][/center]
[b]Note:[/b] I need website developers more than I need server developers!
